# PRD – Task Detail Page

## 1. Purpose

> 👉 *“What exactly needs to be done for this task?”*
> 

This page:

- breaks task into **subtasks**
- gives clarity
- tracks real progress

---

## 2. Route

```bash
/tasks/:taskId
```

---

## 3. Entry Behavior

### On Load:

```bash
GET /api/v1/tasks/:projectId/t/:taskId
```

---

## 4. Page Layout

---

## 🔹 Top Section (Task Context)

**Left:**

- Task Title (large)
- Project Name (small, muted)

**Right:**

- Status badge
- Edit (optional)
- Delete (admin/project_admin)

---

### Metadata Row:

- Assigned user
- Priority
- Deadline

---

## 🔹 Main Section (Subtasks)

This is the **core of the page**

---

## 5. Subtask List

---

### 🧾 Each Subtask:

- Checkbox (complete/incomplete)
- Subtask title
- Delete icon

---

### Behavior:

- Click checkbox → toggle complete
- Instant UI update (optimistic)

---

## 6. Add Subtask

---

### Input:

- Inline input field (not modal)

Example:

```
[ + Add a subtask... ]
```

---

### API:

```bash
POST /api/v1/subtasks/:taskId
```

---

## 7. Progress Indicator (Important)

At top:

> **3 / 5 subtasks completed**
> 

Optional:

- progress bar

---

## 8. Task Status Logic (Important)

---

### Auto behavior (optional but 🔥 if you do it):

- All subtasks complete → task = DONE
- Any subtask incomplete → task ≠ DONE

---

### Manual control (fallback):

- Allow status change like before

---

## 9. States

---

### 🟡 Loading

- Skeleton for:
    - title
    - subtasks

---

### 🔴 Empty

> “No subtasks yet. Break this down.”
> 

---

### ❌ Error

- Retry option

---

## 10. Component Structure

```bash
/pages/tasks/
  TaskDetail.jsx

/components/subtasks/
  SubtaskItem.jsx
  SubtaskList.jsx
  AddSubtaskInput.jsx
  ProgressBar.jsx
```

---

## 11. UX Rules

- No modal for subtasks ❌
- No overdesign ❌
- Fast toggling ✅
- Clear progress ✅

---

## 12. What NOT to Do

- ❌ Don’t add comments (waste of time)
- ❌ Don’t add attachments
- ❌ Don’t build Notion 2.0

Stay focused.

---

## 13. What Makes This Page Good

- You can break a task into steps in seconds
- You see progress instantly
- It feels actionable, not informational

---

## 14. What I Would Do (If I were you)

Build in this order:

1. Fetch + render task
2. Subtask list
3. Toggle complete
4. Add subtask
5. Delete subtask
6. Progress indicator

Done. Move on.